&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LCHS Utilisation Project Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 – Full Time / part time considered flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join us:&lt;/strong&gt; The Spaces and Places team looking for an enthusiastic individual with a ‘can do’ attitude, a passion for delivery and super interpersonal skills to join a small friendly team. The role will be for 18 months (depending on developments) to support the roll out of the LCHS clinical room booking service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18 month fixed term / secondment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Project:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Utilisation Project Officer role will support the Spaces and Places team unlock the efficiencies of better ‘utilisation&#39; of LCHS clinic rooms and other spaces and promote new ways of working and challenging service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will involve&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will take ownership of, managing and implementing this system through effective collaboration, engagement with a variety of stakeholders across the Trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working directly with clinical and admin teams across the County to co-ordinate the roll out of a digital room booking system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with the system supplier (to be confirmed) to ensure the system meets LCHS needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;responsible for delivering communications on project phases, engaging with clinical and admin teams to explain the new system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting team through the delivery and support supplier training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;act at the main contact and priority user for the NHSPS Open Space system (sessional booked spaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with the Team on a daily basis as a mutually supportive unit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the team with utilisation reporting and eventually also support the transition to BAU.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The information from the utilisation system provides rich and detailed information which will be key to decision making for the Trust, our Clinical Leads, finance team and the Space and Places strategic agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
